# ✅ Update parsing logic

Modify your method like this:

```java
private Optional<LocalDate> extractDateFromFileName(String fileName) {
    Matcher matcher = DATE_PATTERN.matcher(fileName);

    if (!matcher.find()) {
        return Optional.empty();
    }

    String dateStr = matcher.group();

    try {
        if (dateStr.contains("-")) {
            return Optional.of(LocalDate.parse(dateStr));
        }

        if (dateStr.length() == 8) {
            return Optional.of(LocalDate.parse(dateStr, DateTimeFormatter.BASIC_ISO_DATE));
        }

        if (dateStr.length() == 12) {
            // yyyyMMddHHmm → take first 8 chars
            String datePart = dateStr.substring(0, 8);
            return Optional.of(LocalDate.parse(datePart, DateTimeFormatter.BASIC_ISO_DATE));
        }

    } catch (Exception e) {
        return Optional.empty();
    }

    return Optional.empty();
}
```

